
[1]serviceable

   SERV'ICEABLE, a.

   1. That does service; that promotes happiness, interest, advantage or
   any good; useful; beneficial; advantageous. Rulers may be very
   serviceable to religion by their example. The attentions of my friends
   were very serviceable to me when abroad. Rain and manure are
   serviceable to land.

   2. Active; diligent; officious.

   I know thee well, a serviceable villain. Shak. [Unusual.]
